reviewText:
PROS:
- Gravlink is kinda nice (a gravity gun that can lower or increase gravity where you shoot);
- Sometimes you'll float at zero-gravity and others you walk on the wall and on the roof, but not at will, you must step on places that change gravity direction (it actually feels like you're on the floor but enemies may look like they are on the walls or on the roof)

CONS:
- 100% linear (you can even press tab to see where you should head next);
- very repetitive;
- too few kinds of enemy;
- at certain point you start to fight one boss right after another (the same bosses);
- strange gameplay: you must use the mini-zoom for the crosshair to appear, otherwise you'll have a programmed inaccuracy that will make you miss a lot of shots; you can't run and shoot at the same time; you can't run laterally; you can't jump!

Overall not recommended, since the gravity play isn't really groundbreaking.
